label.value: Semi-Quantitative Reverse Transcriptase Polymerase Chain Reaction

value.value: A type of reverse transcriptase-polymerase chain reaction combined with electrophoresis. After real-time PCR reaction, amplified gene products undergo electrophoretic separation and the level of expression of the target gene is determined by measuring the intensity of the gel bands corresponding to the target gene amplicon normalized to a housekeeping, internal control gene.

label.value: High Performance Liquid Chromatography/Accelerator Mass Spectrometry

value.value: An analytical technique wherein high performance liquid chromatography is coupled to accelerator mass spectrometry in order to separate, identify, and quantify substances in a sample.

A process to measure the proximity of two fluorochromes whereby the excitation energy of one fluorochrome is released and absorbed by the second fluorochrome. It is used to study interactions and structure of macromolecules. (NCI)

A blood test that exposes a person's T-lymphocytes ex vivo to specific microbial antigen(s) to stimulate the production and release of interferon gamma, which provides an indication that the person has been exposed to a specific microbe.

A method of measuring cardiac output by rapidly injecting a known quantity of dye through a central venous catheter and then monitoring arterial blood at fixed time intervals to determine the change in concentration of dye over time.

A type of blood cell analysis that uses impedance, conductivity, and laser scatter to measure cell volume, cell size, chemical composition, nuclear volume, cellular granularity, nuclear structure, and cell surface characteristics.
A type of computed tomography that is used to construct images of blood vessels.
